.el .ds Aq '
.TH pif-config 1  "pif-config " 
.SH NAME
pif\-config \- Manage pif configuration
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBpif\-config\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Manage pif configuration
.PP
Reads and writes the pif configuration file. The file controls per\-system install directories, the default verbosity level, the system filter used in Auto mode, and version constraints.
.PP
Config file location:
.PP
Linux/macOS  $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/pif/config.yaml Windows      %APPDATA%\\pif\\config.yaml
.PP
Use `pif config show` to view the current file with syntax highlighting.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
pif\-config\-dir(1)
Manage per\-system installation directories
.TP
pif\-config\-verbose(1)
Manage the verbosity level
.TP
pif\-config\-systems(1)
Manage the systems filter (restricts Auto mode to specific systems)
.TP
pif\-config\-versions(1)
Manage per\-system version constraints
.TP
pif\-config\-show(1)
Display the current config file with syntax highlighting
.TP
pif\-config\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
